headline: Accenture CEO on Trade, AI & Political Tensions
summary: Companies are having to navigate economic uncertainty and a shifting geopolitical landscape, that's according to Accenture CEO, Julie Sweet. The consulting and technology giant has been grappling with a pullback in customer spending and greater scrutiny of US government contracts under President Trump. Julie Sweet joined Bloomberg's Francine Lacqua for an interview on how companies like Accenture are able to strategize in a world of global economic uncertainty, investment across industries as well as the role of artificial intelligence.
